        div.clearfix(id="mediaQueries")
          h3 Media Queries
          p Skeleton uses a 
            strong lot
            |  of media queries to serve the scalable grid, but also for the convenience of styling your site on different size screens. Skeleton's media queries are almost exclusively targeted at max and min widths rather than device sizes or orientations. The advantage of this is browsers and future mobile devices that don't map to exact set dimensions will still benefit from the styles. That being said, all of the queries were written to be optimal on Apple iOS devices. The built in media queries include:

          ul.square
            li
              strong Smaller than 960
              | : Smaller than the standard base grid
            li
              strong Tablet Portrait
              | : Between 768px and 959px
            li
              strong All Mobile Sizes
              | : Less than 767px
            li
              strong Just Mobile Landscape
              | : Between 480px and 767px
            li
              strong Just Mobile Portrait
              | : Less than 479px

